CatDescriptText: Harry Burr, laborer, 809 First Street, Coraopolis, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B1 with question: "Do you believe the John James Racket Squad is driving the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "I think that they are doing a good job. However, I don't like the way they run over people without announcing or identifying themselves as police officers."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Harry Burr, wearing light colored shirt with second button unfastened, rolled up cuffs, and cap, standing outside of Jenkins Arcade, with Thrift Drugs in background, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
